<subSubSection id="C301655DFFD0AD04408536FDFEF5FC54" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD0AD04408536FDFDCBFCBC" blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04408536FDFEA1FDBB" bold="true" box="[151,273,501,526]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length of male 
<quantity id="4CE39B33FFD0AD04422136FDFD7CFDB8" box="[563,716,501,525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.245" metricValueMax="4.61" metricValueMin="3.88" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="4.245" valueMax="4.61" valueMin="3.88">3.88–4.61 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04432536FDFCDBFDB8" box="[823,875,501,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.34">4.34</number>
, n = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0443B036FDFC70FDB8" box="[930,960,501,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.0">15</number>
), and female 
<quantity id="4CE39B33FFD0AD04444A36FDFB53FDB8" box="[1112,1251,501,525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.395" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.99" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="4.395" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="3.99">3.99–4.8 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04455C36FDFA32FDB8" box="[1358,1410,501,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.62">4.62</number>
, n = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0440BF3511FF0DFD84" box="[173,189,537,561]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="7.0">7</number>
). Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04416F3512FDA5FD84" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[381,533,537,561]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04416F3512FDA5FD84" box="[381,533,537,561]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but males can be easily distinguished from that species by the presence of a dorsal hair pencil in the hind wing discal cell. In males and females, postmedial border of dorsal forewing orange area less jagged than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04417E356AFDB4FDCC" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[364,516,609,633]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04417E356AFDB4FDCC" box="[364,516,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Dorsal hind wing orange area usually smaller than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD044477356AFB4DFDCC" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1125,1277,609,633]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD044477356AFB4DFDCC" box="[1125,1277,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. General ventral coloration more vivid than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD044203358EFD19FD28" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[529,681,645,669]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD044203358EFD19FD28" box="[529,681,645,669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fresh specimens of both species were compared), making the ventral forewing brown submarginal band darker and better defined. Females are similar to, and difficult to separate from, those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04412835C6FE62FD50" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[314,466,717,741]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04412835C6FE62FD50" box="[314,466,717,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Female ventral forewing brown submarginal band usually solid color, without the ripple pattern usually visible in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0441C935FAFDC3FCBC" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[475,627,753,777]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0441C935FAFDC3FCBC" box="[475,627,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD0AD0440D7341DFEF5FC54" blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0440D7341DFE8AFC9B" bold="true" box="[197,314,789,814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Both the male and female genitalia are similar in size those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD044419341EFB14FC98" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1035,1188,789,813]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD044419341EFB14FC98" box="[1035,1188,789,813]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male specimens (six dissections) varied in the width of the distal half of the valva, and also the number of subterminal spines at the dorsal edge (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD04411A3455FEFFFCC0" box="[264,335,861,885]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0441523455FEFFFCC0" box="[320,335,861,885]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E). The ventral outline of the valva in lateral view was consistent across specimens (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD0445233455FAC8FCC0" box="[1329,1400,861,885]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04457B3455FAC8FCC0" box="[1385,1400,861,885]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Female sterigma with long lateral arms, main plate short and with a shorter midline lobe than 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0444AA348AFA92FC2C" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1208,1314,897,921]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0444AA348AFA92FC2C" box="[1208,1314,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(three dissections). Corpus bursa oval shaped, with paired signa, and constricted at the meeting point with the narrow ductus bursa (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD0440F134C1FE96FC54" box="[227,294,969,993]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04410534C1FE96FC54" box="[279,294,969,993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
