<subSubSection id="C301655DFFD0AD0440D7333DFD46F840" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD0AD0440D7333DFE80F8D0" blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0440D7333DFE44FBFB" bold="true" box="[197,500,1077,1102]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Variation and subspecies.</emphasis>
The local and geographical color variation within 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04443E333EFB39FBF8" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1068,1161,1077,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04443E333EFB39FBF8" box="[1068,1161,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gave rise to the description of several subspecies and forms, and three valid subspecies are currently recognized (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD0AD0444DA3351FA20FBC4" author="Casagrande" box="[1224,1424,1113,1137]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Casagrande, M. M. (2004) Brassolini. p. 201 - 205. In: J. B. Heppner (ed.). Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A Checklist (ed. by G. Lamas). Association of Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific publishers, Gainesville. 439 p." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Casagrande 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0445413351FA20FBC4" box="[1363,1424,1113,1137]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): nominal 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0440E83376FE2EFB20" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[250,414,1149,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0440E83376FE2EFB20" box="[250,414,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="54A08874FFD0AD0441BF3375FE6FFB20" box="[429,479,1149,1173]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
locality: 
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD0442593375FD23FB20" box="[587,659,1149,1173]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0442B53376FCCBFB20" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[679,891,1149,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="didymaon">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0442B53376FCCBFB20" box="[679,891,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea didymaon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD0443993375FC65FB20" box="[907,981,1149,1173]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04440A3376FF68FB0C" authority="Fruhstorfer, 1907" authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="praegrandis">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04440A3376FAB7FB20" box="[1048,1287,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea praegrandis</emphasis>
(Fruhstorfer, 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04408533A9FF60FB0C" box="[151,208,1185,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1907.0">1907</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD0440F533A9FEE6FB0C" box="[231,342,1185,1209]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
). The account for 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04423233AAFDCDFB0C" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[544,637,1185,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04423233AAFDCDFB0C" box="[544,637,1185,1209]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD0AD0442B333A9FCC1FB0C" author="Fruhstorfer" box="[673,881,1185,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04433C33A9FCD8FB0C" box="[814,872,1185,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
is detailed and includes comments on 
<typeStatus id="54A08874FFD0AD04453033AAFAE2FB0F" box="[1314,1362,1186,1210]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
specimens, and from that work it seems that the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04436933CEFC68FB68" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[891,984,1221,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04436933CEFC68FB68" box="[891,984,1221,1245]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Hübner (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04447433CDFB10FB68" box="[1126,1184,1221,1245]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1821.0">1821</number>
) corresponds to a dorsally pale-orange colored specimen in which the delimitation between the dorsal forewing brown edge and orange base is approximately straight. This is the phenotype illustrated by D’Abrera (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04441E3205FBF6FA90" box="[1036,1094,1293,1317]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1987.0">1987</number>
) and 
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD0444953205FB75FA90" box="[1159,1221,1293,1317]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0444A93205FB75FA90" box="[1211,1221,1293,1317]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K (Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro), and according to our samples it seems to be a less common phenotype than that in 
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD04452C3239FA31FAFC" box="[1342,1409,1329,1353]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0445643239FA31FAFC" box="[1398,1409,1329,1353]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E. Although wing color and shape differences between 
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD0442FE325DFC9AFAD8" box="[748,810,1365,1389]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD044332325DFC9AFAD8" box="[800,810,1365,1389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K and 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD044369325DFC35FAD8" box="[891,901,1365,1389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
E seem extreme, we have examined specimens with intermediate phenotypes from several locations including Nova Friburgo itself, and also Serra do Caraça (Minas Gerais), and São Paulo, and there are no obvious differences between male genitalia of these forms. From this we conclude that, as currently understood, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0442B932CAFCFFFA6C" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[683,847,1473,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0442B932CAFCFFFA6C" box="[683,847,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a broad range of color variation, and subspecific definition within 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04418B32EEFE48FA48" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[409,504,1509,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04418B32EEFE48FA48" box="[409,504,1509,1533]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore problematic. Although one specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD04446832EEFB52FA4B" box="[1146,1250,1510,1534]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(Caazapá, P. N. Caaguazú) examined from a photograph matches the defining characters given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD0AD0444493101FA9EF994" author="Fruhstorfer" box="[1115,1326,1545,1569]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0444F93101FA96F994" box="[1259,1318,1545,1569]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0445763102FE90F9F0" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="praegrandis">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0445763102FE90F9F0" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. b. praegrandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we found that such characters fit within the range of variation observed for 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04449E3126FA81F9F0" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1164,1329,1581,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04449E3126FA81F9F0" box="[1164,1329,1581,1605]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD0445453125FA2CF9F0" box="[1367,1436,1581,1605]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(photographs of a Paraguayan specimen were provided by S. Rios, specimen from the Museo Nacional de Historia Natural del 
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD04410D317EFE37F93B" box="[287,391,1654,1678]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
collection). Therefore, the status of this subspecies should be verified by examination of a series of specimens. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD0AD04416D3191FDFFF904" author="Fruhstorfer" box="[383,591,1689,1713]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04421E3191FDF6F904" box="[524,582,1689,1713]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that the width of the dorsal forewing dark brown area is narrowest at the northern part of the species distribution, progressively becoming broader towards southern localities in 
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD04454A31B5FA2DF960" box="[1368,1437,1725,1749]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(and probably 
<collectingCountry id="F30C7646FFD0AD04412B31E9FE10F94C" box="[313,416,1761,1785]" name="Uruguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
). We confirmed his assessment, and southern specimens with little or no orange color distal from the dorsal forewing discal cell correspond to the described 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD044366300EFBF9F8A8" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[884,1097,1797,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="didymaon">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD044366300EFBF9F8A8" box="[884,1097,1797,1821]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea didymaon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD0AD044448300DFB29F8A8" box="[1114,1177,1797,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04449D300DFB29F8A8" box="[1167,1177,1797,1821]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
H and I). Nonetheless, we feel that the local and clinal variation in color pattern in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04435E3022FC1BF8F4" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[844,939,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04435E3022FC1BF8F4" box="[844,939,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
calls the recognition of discrete subspecies into question.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD0AD0440D7307AFD46F840" blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0440D7307AFE60F83F" bold="true" box="[197,464,1905,1930]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Natural history notes.</emphasis>
The early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0442D0307AFC92F83C" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[706,802,1905,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0442D0307AFC92F83C" box="[706,802,1905,1929]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not been described. André Freitas (pers. comm.) observed females of this species ovipositing on an unidentified grass, and notes that adults can be locally common on forest edges bordered by wet to flooded grassland in higher altitude localities. Reported host plants include 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04408530D5FEA2F840" box="[151,274,2013,2037]" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="family">Gramineae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04415A30D6FE0DF843" box="[328,445,2014,2038]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD0AD0441EA30D5FD5AF840" author="Beccaloni" box="[504,746,2013,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Beccaloni, G. W., Viloria, A. L., Hall, S. K. &amp; Robinson, G. S. (2008) Catalogue of the hostplants of the Neotropical butterflies. Natural History Museum, London, 536 pp." type="book" year="2008">
Beccaloni 
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04427C30D6FD16F840" box="[622,678,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD0442BF30D5FD5AF840" box="[685,746,2013,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
